Colleges that Teach Traditional ...

The Atia School is a K-6 elementary school consisting of a boys division and a girls division as well as a secondary school which offers grades 7 through 10. After Atia, there are both public and private secondary (high) schools in Monrovia to choose from. In addition to the regionally located public high schools in the capital, the International School of Liberia (ISL) as well as a number of other private elementary and high schools in Monrovia primarily serve the foreign population. Although these schools are private, most are regarded as generally higher quality than the publicly funded schools. A student can reasonably expect to pay a significant tuitional fee to attend a Western-style secondary school in Liberia, but the investment may be worth it to the right student.

School Sports & Activities in Liberia
